   <abstract xlink:href="http://lib.lsu.edu/services/oralhistory/abstracts/mckinley/1_history/Smith_Charles_T936.pdf">Smith describes McKinley High School's impact on Baton Rouge's racial, political,
            economic and social history. He recalls the importance of academics, athletics, and
            school pride during his years as a student there in the 1940s. He lists his role models,
            inspiring teachers and his accomplishments.</abstract>
